      <h3>ICEBERG Is NOT Right For You If:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You're brand new to nicotine pouches (ICEBERG's entry tier is still strong relative to beginner brands).</li>
        <li>You're seeking casual, social nicotine consumption.</li>
        <li>You have cardiovascular disease, nicotine sensitivity, or anxiety disorders.</li>
        <li>You're pregnant, nursing, or under 18 years old.</li>
        <li>You're on medications that interact with nicotine (talk to your doctor first).</li>
        <li>You dislike strong flavours; ICEBERG's offerings are assertive.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Best Entry Point</h3>
      <p>If you're curious about ICEBERG but have limited ultra-strength experience, start with Mint Explosion or Menthol at 6mg. Use one pouch per day for a week. If well-tolerated, progress to a 30mg variant. Only after consistent 30mg use should you consider the 40mg Ultra tier.</p>
