    <section>
      <h2>Safety and Responsible Use</h2>
      <p>ICEBERG's strength demands respect. This section covers critical safety considerations for ultra-high-nicotine consumption.</p>

      <h3>Start Low, Even Within ICEBERG</h3>
      <p>ICEBERG's lowest option (6mg) is already potent. Do not assume that because you've used nicotine before, you can handle 30mg on your first try. Nicotine tolerance is individual and context-dependent. A former heavy smoker might handle 30mg fine; a casual former smoker could get seriously ill.</p>

      <h3>Never Double Up</h3>
      <p>Using two ICEBERG pouches simultaneously or consecutively (before the first has finished) is a direct path to nicotine poisoning. Space pouches by at least 2-3 hours, and use only one pouch per day while establishing your tolerance.</p>

      <h3>Hydration Is Non-Negotiable</h3>
      <p>Nicotine is dehydrating. Drink water before, during, and after using ICEBERG pouches. Dehydration amplifies negative side effects (dizziness, nausea, tremors). A simple rule: if you use high-strength pouches, you need proportionally higher water intake.</p>

      <h3>Recognize Warning Signs</h3>
      <p>These are normal at high strengths and typically resolve within an hour:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Mild dizziness or lightheadedness</li>
        <li>Slight nausea</li>
        <li>Jitteriness or tremors</li>
        <li>Elevated heart rate</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>These indicate serious problems; remove the pouch and seek medical attention:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Severe vomiting</li>
        <li>Chest pain or irregular heartbeat</li>
        <li>Seizures or loss of consciousness</li>
        <li>Difficulty breathing</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Medical Consultation</h3>
      <p>If you have any pre-existing health conditions—cardiovascular disease, diabetes, anxiety disorders, nicotine sensitivity—consult your doctor before using ICEBERG products. They can assess your individual risk and advise on safe use (if any).</p>
      <p>For clinical context on nicotine poisoning risks and symptoms, see <a href="https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/21582-nicotine-poisoning">Cleveland Clinic's guide to nicotine poisoning</a>.</p>

      <h3>Never Combine Nicotine Products</h3>
      <p>Do not use ICEBERG pouches alongside cigarettes, snus, vapes, or other nicotine products. This dramatically increases overdose risk and is how most nicotine poisoning cases occur.</p>
    </section>

