    <section>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>What is the strongest ICEBERG nicotine pouch at SnusFriend?</h3>
      <p>At SnusFriend, ICEBERG's strongest products are the 40mg variants: Bubblegum (EU), Emerald Ultra (EU), and Grape (EU). These are at the absolute top of the strength spectrum and should only be used by experienced nicotine consumers with well-established tolerance.</p>

      <h3>Are ICEBERG pouches suitable for beginners?</h3>
      <p>ICEBERG is NOT recommended for nicotine pouch beginners. Even their entry-level 6mg options are geared toward experienced users. Beginners should start with 3-5mg brands from manufacturers specifically designing for new users. If you're curious about ICEBERG, only try it after establishing tolerance with milder strengths.</p>

      <h3>What's the most popular ICEBERG flavour?</h3>
      <p>Strawberry Mango and Strawberry Pomegranate Extreme are among the most beloved ICEBERG products, with consistent 4.5+ star ratings. These deliver bold berry flavour alongside aggressive nicotine profiles. Mint Explosion (6mg) is also popular for users seeking milder entry-level strength.</p>

      <h3>How long does an ICEBERG pouch last?</h3>
      <p>Most ICEBERG pouches last 30-50 minutes, depending on individual absorption rates, pouch moisture, and the specific strength. Higher-strength variants (30mg+) may feel shorter due to intensity. If a pouch feels too mild, check that you're using the correct strength tier.</p>

      <h3>Why is ICEBERG called 'ultra-strength'?</h3>
      <p>ICEBERG is known as the 'ultra-strength specialist' because it offers an aggressive range of high-nicotine concentrations (up to 40mg at SnusFriend) combined with potent, icy flavours. Even their lower-strength options (6mg) are formulated for intensity rather than casual consumption. The brand's philosophy is unapologetic strength for experienced users.</p>
